  Locus:
    Page: 415
    Verse: 19
Tags:
  - Selfishness
---
Self-love cannot endure to see itself; it would die of shame and vexation!
If by chance it gets a glimpse, it at once places itself in some artificial
light, as to soften the full hideousness and find some comfort.
